# =============================================================================
# Rust / Cargo
# =============================================================================
debug/
target/
# Cargo.lock IS committed for this workspace (binary crates: uffs-cli,
# uffs-daemon, uffs-mcp, etc.).  Committing it is required for:
#   * Reproducible builds (every dev + CI + release resolves the same graph)
#   * Supply-chain integrity (pairs with cargo-vet + cargo-deny pinning)
#   * SLSA attestation integrity (release provenance references a specific
#     dep graph; without Cargo.lock that graph would drift every run)
#   * cargo-vet stability (exemptions are keyed on specific crate-versions
#     — a floating Cargo.lock would break cargo vet check on every
#     unrelated upstream patch release)
# To deliberately update deps, use `cargo update` or a Dependabot PR.
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb
# macOS sed -i backup files
*.toml-e
*.yml-e
*.rs-e

# =============================================================================
# Trash / quarantine (local rollback staging)
# =============================================================================
/_trash/*
!/_trash/.gitignore
/_trash/**/.gitkeep
/_trash/**/.keep

# =============================================================================
# Build artifacts & generated binaries
# =============================================================================
build/
*.rlib
*.bin
/test_scf

# =============================================================================
# Logs, vendor, misc
# =============================================================================
/Shell/
# /LOG/ is strictly local-only.  Every file under it — runtime logs
# (defender ETLs, mental_health, `ship_run*.log` captures), per-session
# notes, healing logs, assessment scratchpads, anything — stays on the
# developer's machine and NEVER reaches git.  The project-level
# `CHANGELOG.md` at the repo root is the only changelog that ships.
/LOG/
/vendor/
/missing_paths.txt
/_trash/
/reference/
# Binaries are distributed via GitHub Releases, not committed to the repo
dist/
# Transient pipeline / debug logs captured at the workspace root via `tee`.
# Kept around between healing iterations but never committed.
/.ship_run*.log
/.clippy_run*.log
/.git_status.txt
/.git_show.txt
/.git_lsfiles.txt

